        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare genetic primary immunodeficiency characterized by increased susceptibility to fungal infections typically manifesting as recurrent chronic mucocutaneous candidiasis systemic candidiasis with meningoencephalitis and deep dermatophystosis with dermatophytes invading skin hair nails lymph nodes and brain resulting in erythematosquamous lesions nodular subcutaneous or ulcerative infiltrations severe onychomycosis and lymphadenopathy."
